<title>USA: Informix says no profit until year-end.</title>
<headline>Informix says no profit until year-end.</headline>
<dateline>PALO ALTO, Calif. 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Informix Corp Chief Executive Phil White said Thursday his software company will not have a profit until the end of the year.</p>
<p>&quot;We are looking at profits going out of 1997,&quot; White said in an interview.</p>
<p>Informix, a database software publisher, on Friday reported a loss of $140.1 million or $0.93 per share for the first quarter. Revenue fell 34 percent to $133.7 million.</p>
<p>Informix unveiled a restructuring plan to get sales going again.</p>
